{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Php|2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","chapter":2,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":1,"text":"If, then, there is any encouragement in Christ, if any consolation of love, if any fellowship with the Spirit, if any affection and mercy,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":2,"text":"make my joy complete by thinking the same way, having the same love, united in spirit, intent on one purpose.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":3,"text":"Do nothing out of selfish ambition or conceit, but in humility consider others as more important than yourselves.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":4,"text":"Everyone should look not to his own interests, but rather to the interests of others.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":5,"text":"Adopt the same attitude as that of Christ Jesus,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":6,"text":"who, existing in the form of God,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":7,"text":"Instead he emptied himself","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":8,"text":"he humbled himself by becoming obedient","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":9,"text":"For this reason God highly exalted him","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":10,"text":"so that at the name of Jesus","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":11,"text":"and every tongue will confess","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":12,"text":"Therefore, my dear friends, just as you have always obeyed, so now, not only in my presence but even more in my absence, work out your own salvation with fear and trembling.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":13,"text":"For it is God who is working in you both to will and to work according to his good purpose.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":14,"text":"Do everything without grumbling and arguing,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":15,"text":"so that you may be blameless and pure, children of God who are faultless in a crooked and perverted generation, among whom you shine like stars in the world,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":16,"text":"by holding firm to the word of life. Then I can boast in the day of Christ that I didn’t run or labor for nothing.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":17,"text":"But even if I am poured out as a drink offering on the sacrificial service of your faith, I am glad and rejoice with all of you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":18,"text":"In the same way you should also be glad and rejoice with me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":19,"text":"Now I hope in the Lord Jesus to send Timothy to you soon so that I too may be encouraged by news about you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":20,"text":"For I have no one else like-minded who will genuinely care about your interests;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":21,"text":"all seek their own interests, not those of Jesus Christ.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":22,"text":"But you know his proven character, because he has served with me in the gospel ministry like a son with a father.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":23,"text":"Therefore, I hope to send him as soon as I see how things go with me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":24,"text":"I am confident in the Lord that I myself will also come soon.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":25,"text":"But I considered it necessary to send you Epaphroditus —my brother, coworker, and fellow soldier, as well as your messenger and minister to my need —","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":26,"text":"since he has been longing for all of you and was distressed because you heard that he was sick.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":27,"text":"Indeed, he was so sick that he nearly died. However, God had mercy on him, and not only on him but also on me, so that I would not have sorrow upon sorrow.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":28,"text":"For this reason, I am very eager to send him so that you may rejoice again when you see him and I may be less anxious.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":29,"text":"Therefore, welcome him in the Lord with great joy and hold people like him in honor,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","bookOrder":49,"chapter":2,"verse":30,"text":"because he came close to death for the work of Christ, risking his life to make up what was lacking in your ministry to me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Php","chapter":2,"paragraphStarts":[1,5,6,7,8,9,10,11,12,19,25],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Christian Humility"},{"beforeVerse":5,"text":"Christ’s Humility and Exaltation"},{"beforeVerse":12,"text":"Lights in the World"},{"beforeVerse":19,"text":"Timothy and Epaphroditus"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Php:2:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"If, then, there is any encouragement in Christ, if any consolation of love, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 5:8","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 15:30","book":"Rom","chapter":15,"verse":30,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Th 2:16","book":"2Th","chapter":2,"verse":16,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Jn 3:16","book":"1Jn","chapter":3,"verse":16,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Jn 4:9–10","book":"1Jn","chapter":4,"verse":9,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Jn 4:16","book":"1Jn","chapter":4,"verse":16,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" if any fellowship with the Spirit, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 12:13","book":"1Co","chapter":12,"verse":13,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 13:13","book":"2Co","chapter":13,"verse":13,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Eph 4:3","book":"Eph","chapter":4,"verse":3,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"text","text":" if any affection and mercy, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Col 3:12","book":"Col","chapter":3,"verse":12,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 5:8","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":8},{"label":"Rm 15:30","book":"Rom","chapter":15,"verse":30},{"label":"2Th 2:16","book":"2Th","chapter":2,"verse":16},{"label":"1Jn 3:16","book":"1Jn","chapter":3,"verse":16},{"label":"1Jn 4:9–10","book":"1Jn","chapter":4,"verse":9},{"label":"1Jn 4:16","book":"1Jn","chapter":4,"verse":16},{"lab